      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>The Origin Story</h2>
        <p>Ad-Apt started long before the name existed. In 2011, I started Socialated in a spare bedroom with $1,000. It grew into a 13-person full-service marketing agency servicing clients worldwide. In 2014, Socialated was acquired by Virsocom Ventures.</p>
        <p>After the acquisition, I formed <strong>Lucas Sommer Inc.</strong> in 2014 and have held it ever since. My colleague Bryan Lozano — who had been a partner at Socialated — formed <strong>Bryan Lozano Inc.</strong> We both continued doing marketing work independently, building our own client bases and expertise. Eventually, we merged the two companies to create <strong>Ad-Apt</strong> — two proven operators combining forces under one roof.</p>
        <p>Today Ad-Apt is a full-service digital marketing agency working with businesses, brands, and entrepreneurs across web development, SEO, paid media, social media, email marketing, mobile apps, API development, and hosting.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Results That Matter</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Payless ShoeSource</strong> — 400% ROAS. 1,200% e-commerce transaction growth. PPC optimization, SEO, technical web improvements, and Mailchimp email automation. <em>"I have truly enjoyed working with your team. You've been brilliant."</em> — Cheri Bernard, Sr. Manager Global Marketing</li>
          <li><strong>True Blue Car Wash</strong> — $1M+ in new sales. 500% increase in subscription revenue. Hundreds of new page-one rankings. Thousands of conversions. CRO, SEO, mobile app development, marketing automation, media production, and email.</li>
          <li><strong>Teton Gravity Research</strong> — 500% sales increase. 7.2x ROAS. Google Ads, Facebook Ads, Shopify CRO, and Klaviyo email/SMS automation for the outdoor media brand.</li>
          <li><strong>LeadsRx</strong> — 300% increase in demo requests through SEO and content marketing for the B2B attribution SaaS platform. (LeadsRx was later acquired by Unbounce.)</li>
          <li><strong>Boss PDX</strong> — $0 to $1M in annual sales. Full digital buildout from scratch: web dev, SEO, Google Ads, PPC, display, retargeting, Google My Business, mobile app, and branding.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

